    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26c.60-61_0001"/>
                
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>Border of Roses and Music Notes</figDesc>
                </figure>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        State Hospital No. I.
                        Fulton, Mo.
                        Nov. 15, 1958
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John Niehar<del>t</del><add>dt</add><sic>Neihardt</sic></addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Route 7. SkyRim<sic>Skyrim</sic> Farm.</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>>Columbia, Mo.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>My dear Mr. Niehar<del>t</del><add>dt</add><sic>Neihardt</sic></salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Recevied the loving letter from your happy Skyrim Farm and treasure it &#8212; especially your <del>g</del><add>G</add>ood Wishes; Thank you So Much.</p>
                
                <p>I am learning sewing + I have done a litte extra work + earned enough to buy 2 of my best young friends a gift my own self (along with handmade article) + am proud of it. I hope to get Decorated Communion Candles for my 3 children. I myself have one that I treasure.</p>
                
                <p>Hoping for <unclear>you a</unclear> happy Thanksgiving (so American) + Holiday Season.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Gratefully yours,</salute>
                
                    <signed>(Mrs.) Lucille M. Wolf.</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">60</fw>
                
                <note type="authorial">
                    Geraldine Joyce
                    Ronald LeRoy        }Wolf
                    Damian Jerome
                
                    my childrens' name.
                </note>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26c.60-61_0002"/> 
                
                <note type="curatorial"><hi rend="caps">JOHN G. NEIHARDT CENTER</hi></note>
                
                <note type="authorial">
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John Niehardt<sic>Niehardt</sic></addrLine>
                            <addrLine>Route 7</addrLine>
                                <addrLine>Columbia</addrLine>
                                    <addrLine>Mo.</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Skyrim Farm</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </note>
                
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26c.60-61_0003"/>
                
                <ab type="return">
                    <add><hi rend="caps">RCR</hi></add>
                        <lb/>
                    <hi rend="caps">AFTER 5 DAYS RETURN TO
                        <lb/>
                    STATE HOSPITAL</hi> No. 1
                        <lb/>
                    <hi rend="caps">FULTON, MO.</hi>
                </ab>
                
                <ab type="postmark">
                    FULTON
                    NOV17'58
                    MO.
                    
                    P.B.METER
                    165793
                </ab>
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>4 Cent Stamp stamped on envelope</figDesc>
                    <p>U.S. POSTAGE
                    04</p>
                </figure>
                
                <ab type="address">
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John Niehardt<sic>Neihardt</sic></addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Route # 7</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </ab>
                
                <fw type="curtorial">61</fw>
                
            </div1>
